cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL. 

This paper proposes a neural network to learn a generative model for indoor scene layouts, which is applicable to several computer vision tasks such as 3D pose and layout estimation from RGB-D data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning a generative model through a grammar-based auto-encoder, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with reasoning about object co-occurrences in training data, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
